dct_description_sm: Printed with vegetation. Prepared under the direction of the Chief of Engineers by the Army Map Service (AM), Corps of Engineers, Department of the Army , original map compiled by planetable surveys by USGS. Variant title: Indiana 1:25,000. Filing title: Jeffersonville, Ind.-KY. Standard map series designation: AMS (Series) V851 Sheet 3860 I SW. First edition--AMS 1. "A.M.S. Series V851" "Transverse Mercator projection." Relief shown by contours and spot heights. Shows roads, railroads, boundaries, schools, churches, cemeteries, mines, and natural features. "Contour interval 10 feet." Marginal maps: Index to boundaries.--Index to adjoining sheets. "Scale changed, marginal data revised and Universal Transverse Mercator Grid added, 1947. Copied in 1947 from Indiana, 1:24,000, USGS, Jeffersonville, 1946. Original map compiled by planetable surveys by USGS. Horizontal and vertical control by USGS and USC&GS and Corps of Engineers, U. S. Army. Map field checked." "N3815-W8537.5/7.5." "2-1948." "First edition (AMS 1), 1947."
Imprint: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, Corps of Engineers, War Department, 1947.
Dimensions: 56 x 45 cm or smaller; Scale: 1:25,000
dct_creator_sm: Geological Survey (U.S.); United States. Army Map Service
